<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-13394] Topic IDs should be removed from PartitionFetchState if they are no longer sent by the controller</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13394</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-13102&quot; title=&quot;Topic IDs not propagated to metadata cache quickly enough for Fetch path&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-13102&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-13102&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we added topic IDs to the InitialFetchState and the PartitionFetchState in order to send fetch requests using topic IDs when ibp is 3.1.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, there are some cases where we could initially send topic IDs from the controller and then no longer to do so (controller changes to an IBP &amp;lt; 2.8). If we do not remove from the PartitionFetchState and one broker is still IBP 3.1, it will try to send a version 13 fetch request to brokers that no longer have topic IDs in the metadata cache. This could leave the cluster in a state unable to fetch from these partitions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
